<br>
A good moderator will make the rules crystal clear, will enforce them consistantly and uniformly (as much as they are able given time constraints, etc) and fairly.  I think our mods have been doing a great job in the time I've been here, but I still think there's room for improvement.  The most important thing is that they seem to be learning as they go.<br>
<br>
I've seen a board fall apart due to moderators taking the wrong approach towards a close knit posting base of users.  I've seen that same board come back and become active again because of a change in moderation.  Moderators do make a difference to a board.  Bad moderation is far easier to see than good moderation, however.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title><A HREF="http://www.ezboard.com/promotions/csc.html" TARGET="_blank" ><IMG SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/image/cscicon3.gif" WIDTH="20" HEIGHT="20" BORDER="0" align="absmiddle"></A> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/usarhea.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Sarhea</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_redspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Tu'Rilthiil Bladedancer</span><br>  Posts: 1513<br> <font color=#A62A2A>(9/16/02 12:40:00 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm4.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=1385.topic&index=34>Reply</a>    <br>ezSupporter<br> <BR><img src=http://sarshouse.homestead.com/files/images/sar.gif width=52 height=126></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: I want new Mods</span><hr size=1> Ermok never bitched about my modding, Val.<br>
